{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01BWbMYeDSqxq1FVejXYr7vb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MdX1CdPpCzgfBNdGacVa9k","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"grep -A 30 \"agent_command\\|agent_args\" /workspace/docs/USAGE.md | head -60","description":"Extract agent configuration details from docs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4301,"cache_read_input_tokens":37774,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4301,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AkfWUPgq78MP7yViLUjjcD","session_id":"abc5f750-0862-4f12-8214-59a5ee9bdc43","uuid":"ff0e30be-3e44-4e66-91d0-6332698ec0c0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MdX1CdPpCzgfBNdGacVa9k","type":"tool_result","content":"  agent_command = \"aider\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\nOr at the workflow level via a `container` block:\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nOr globally via `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable.\n\nPriority (highest to lowest): step-level `agent_command`, workflow-level\n`container { agent_command }`, `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env var, default (`claude`).\n\n### Agent Fallback Chains\n\nUse a comma-separated list in `agent_command` to configure fallback chains. If\nthe first agent errors without reporting a result, the system tries the next:\n\n```\nstep implement {\n  prompt = \"...\"\n  agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\nFallback rules:\n- **Command not found or failed to start** — fall back to next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — fall back to next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** — use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** — step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** — step returns `fail`\n\nKnown agents have default arguments (e.g., Claude gets\n`-p --output-format text --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Other agents receive\nthe prompt on stdin with no extra flags. Override with `agent_args` at the step\nor workflow level.\n\n## Result Protocol\n\nSteps report results by writing a marker to stdout:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\nFor script steps, if no marker is written, the exit code determines the result:\n0 = `success`, non-zero = `fail`. Agent steps follow the same convention.\n\n## Prompt Assembly","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AkfWUPgq78MP7yViLUjjcD","session_id":"abc5f750-0862-4f12-8214-59a5ee9bdc43","uuid":"b2180eeb-31d5-490c-98e2-3d016bf16795"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_progress","task_id":"a946cca981e1ccd3f","tool_use_id":"toolu_01AkfWUPgq78MP7yViLUjjcD","description":"Reading internal/orchestrator/mergeagent.go","usage":{"total_tokens":50062,"tool_uses":30,"duration_ms":19496},"last_tool_name":"Read","uuid":"326fcd78-d314-4ce5-8b39-3bd10e4a69fa","session_id":"abc5f750-0862-4f12-8214-59a5ee9bdc43"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_014narhA1w6c34iXVzG14ccp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HsLjzGzdXR1nc9Zwj3WviM","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/internal/orchestrator/mergeagent.go"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7751,"cache_read_input_tokens":42075,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7751,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AkfWUPgq78MP7yViLUjjcD","session_id":"abc5f750-0862-4f12-8214-59a5ee9bdc43","uuid":"e3f9915d-d44a-4d19-a802-2f338ab3b933"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HsLjzGzdXR1nc9Zwj3WviM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package orchestrator\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bytes\"\n     5→\t\"context\"\n     6→\t\"fmt\"\n     7→\t\"log\"\n     8→\t\"os\"\n     9→\t\"os/exec\"\n    10→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    11→\n    12→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    13→)\n    14→\n    15→// MergeAgent merges feature branches into main using rebase-first strategy.\n    16→// On conflict, it prefers main's version (-X ours from the feature branch's\n    17→// perspective). If rebase fails entirely, the merge is flagged as failed and\n    18→// the branch is preserved for human review.\n    19→type MergeAgent struct {\n    20→\tMergeQueue ports.MergeQueueStore\n    21→\tValidate   string // optional validation command (e.g. \"make test\")\n    22→}\n    23→\n    24→// gitEnv returns environment variables for cloche git operations.\n    25→func gitEnv() []string {\n    26→\treturn append(os.Environ(),\n    27→\t\t\"GIT_AUTHOR_NAME=cloche\", \"GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL=cloche@local\",\n    28→\t\t\"GIT_COMMITTER_NAME=cloche\", \"GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL=cloche@local\",\n    29→\t)\n    30→}\n    31→\n    32→// Merge takes a merge queue entry and rebases its branch onto main, then\n    33→// fast-forwards main to the rebased HEAD.\n    34→//\n    35→// Strategy:\n    36→//  1. Create a worktree checked out at the feature branch\n    37→//  2. Rebase onto main with -X ours (prefer main on conflict)\n    38→//  3. On success: update-ref main to rebased HEAD, delete branch\n    39→//  4. On failure: abort rebase, flag as failed, preserve branch\n    40→func (m *MergeAgent) Merge(ctx context.Context, entry *ports.MergeQueueEntry, projectDir string) error {\n    41→\tworktreeDir := filepath.Join(projectDir, \".gitworktrees\", \"merge\", entry.RunID)\n    42→\tif err := os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(worktreeDir), 0755); err != nil {\n    43→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"creating worktree parent: %w\", err)\n    44→\t}\n    45→\n    46→\t// Create worktree at the feature branch\n    47→\taddCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"git\", \"worktree\", \"add\", worktreeDir, entry.Branch)\n    48→\taddCmd.Dir = projectDir\n    49→\tif out, err := addCmd.CombinedOutput(); err != nil {\n    50→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"git worktree add: %s: %w\", out, err)\n    51→\t}\n    52→\n    53→\tremoveWorktree := func() {\n    54→\t\trmCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"git\", \"worktree\", \"remove\", \"--force\", worktreeDir)\n    55→\t\trmCmd.Dir = projectDir\n    56→\t\trmCmd.Run()\n    57→\t}\n    58→\n    59→\tenv := gitEnv()\n    60→\n    61→\t// Rebase the feature branch onto main, preferring main on conflict\n    62→\trebaseCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"git\", \"rebase\", \"-X\", \"ours\", \"main\")\n    63→\trebaseCmd.Dir = worktreeDir\n    64→\trebaseCmd.Env = env\n    65→\tif out, err := rebaseCmd.CombinedOutput(); err != nil {\n    66→\t\t// Rebase failed — abort and preserve branch for human review\n    67→\t\tabortRebase(ctx, worktreeDir)\n    68→\t\tremoveWorktree()\n    69→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"rebase failed (branch preserved for review): %s: %w\", out, err)\n    70→\t}\n    71→\n    72→\t// Run validation if configured\n    73→\tif m.Validate != \"\" {\n    74→\t\tvalidateCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"sh\", \"-c\", m.Validate)\n    75→\t\tvalidateCmd.Dir = worktreeDir\n    76→\t\tvalidateCmd.Env = env\n    77→\t\tif out, err := validateCmd.CombinedOutput(); err != nil {\n    78→\t\t\tremoveWorktree()\n    79→\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"validation failed: %s: %w\", out, err)\n    80→\t\t}\n    81→\t}\n    82→\n    83→\t// Fast-forward main to the rebased HEAD\n    84→\theadCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"HEAD\")\n    85→\theadCmd.Dir = worktreeDir\n    86→\trebasedHead, err := headCmd.Output()\n    87→\tif err != nil {\n    88→\t\tremoveWorktree()\n    89→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"rev-parse HEAD: %w\", err)\n    90→\t}\n    91→\n    92→\t// Must remove worktree before updating main ref and deleting branch,\n    93→\t// because git won't allow deleting a branch checked out in a worktree.\n    94→\tremoveWorktree()\n    95→\n    96→\tupdateCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"git\", \"update-ref\", \"refs/heads/main\",\n    97→\t\tstring(bytes.TrimSpace(rebasedHead)))\n    98→\tupdateCmd.Dir = projectDir\n    99→\tif out, err := updateCmd.CombinedOutput(); err != nil {\n   100→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"update-ref main: %s: %w\", out, err)\n   101→\t}\n   102→\n   103→\t// Delete the feature branch\n   104→\tdelCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"git\", \"branch\", \"-D\", entry.Branch)\n   105→\tdelCmd.Dir = projectDir\n   106→\tif out, err := delCmd.CombinedOutput(); err != nil {\n   107→\t\tlog.Printf(\"merge-agent: warning: failed to delete branch %s: %s: %v\", entry.Branch, out, err)\n   108→\t}\n   109→\n   110→\treturn nil\n   111→}\n   112→\n   113→// ProcessQueue dequeues the next pending merge and processes it.\n   114→// Returns true if a merge was processed, false if the queue was empty or busy.\n   115→func (m *MergeAgent) ProcessQueue(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) bool {\n   116→\tentry, err := m.MergeQueue.NextPendingMerge(ctx, projectDir)\n   117→\tif err != nil {\n   118→\t\tlog.Printf(\"merge-agent: failed to dequeue: %v\", err)\n   119→\t\treturn false\n   120→\t}\n   121→\tif entry == nil {\n   122→\t\treturn false\n   123→\t}\n   124→\n   125→\tlog.Printf(\"merge-agent: processing merge for run %s (branch %s)\", entry.RunID, entry.Branch)\n   126→\n   127→\tif err := m.Merge(ctx, entry, projectDir); err != nil {\n   128→\t\tlog.Printf(\"merge-agent: merge failed for run %s: %v\", entry.RunID, err)\n   129→\t\t_ = m.MergeQueue.FailMerge(ctx, entry.RunID)\n   130→\t\treturn true\n   131→\t}\n   132→\n   133→\tlog.Printf(\"merge-agent: merge succeeded for run %s\", entry.RunID)\n   134→\t_ = m.MergeQueue.CompleteMerge(ctx, entry.RunID)\n   135→\n   136→\t// Try to process the next entry in the queue\n   137→\tm.ProcessQueue(ctx, projectDir)\n   138→\treturn true\n   139→}\n   140→\n   141→// abortRebase runs git rebase --abort to clean up a failed rebase.\n   142→func abortRebase(ctx context.Context, worktreeDir string) {\n   143→\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"git\", \"rebase\", \"--abort\")\n   144→\tcmd.Dir = worktreeDir\n   145→\tcmd.Run()\n   146→}\n   147→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AkfWUPgq78MP7yViLUjjcD","session_id":"abc5f750-0862-4f12-8214-59a5ee9bdc43","uuid":"e36109eb-5eb6-41ae-ad60-afcc05ee86a7"}
