on-zero with result marker\n- Returns \"fail\" if last command crashes without marker\n- Returns error only if all commands fail to start\n\n**Default Arguments:**\n- Claude: `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`\n- Other agents: no default args (prompt on stdin only)\n\n**Prompt Assembly (in `assemblePrompt()`):**\n1. Step's `prompt` config (inline or from `file()`)\n2. User prompt from `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n3. Validation feedback from `.cloche/output/*.log` (if `feedback: \"true\"`)\n4. Result selection instructions (lists all declared results with `CLOCHE_RESULT:` prefix)\n\n**Streaming Support:**\n- Parses `stream-json` format from Claude\n- Extracts `text_delta` events for live output\n- Also handles final result events\n\n**Retry Logic:**\n- Tracks attempt count in `.cloche/attempt_count/<step>`\n- Returns \"give-up\" when `max_attempts` exceeded\n- Increments on each call\n\n---\n\n### 3. Domain Types Related to Agents\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` and `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**Step Structure:**\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType              // StepTypeAgent, StepTypeScript, StepTypeWorkflow\n    Results []string              // Declared possible outcomes\n    Config  map[string]string     // Configuration key-value pairs\n}\n```\n\n**Step Types (Inferred from Config):**\n- `StepTypeAgent`: Has `prompt` field → uses prompt adapter\n- `StepTypeScript`: Has `run` field → uses generic adapter\n- `StepTypeWorkflow`: Has `workflow_name` field (for sub-workflows)\n\n**Key Agent-Related Config Keys:**\n- `prompt`: Template or inline prompt text (or `file(\"path\")`)\n- `agent_command`: Comma-separated fallback chain (e.g. \"claude,gemini\")\n- `agent_args`: Override default arguments\n- `max_attempts`: Limit retries (step returns \"give-up\" when exhausted)\n- `feedback`: \"true\" to include previous validation output in prompt\n- `timeout`: Step timeout duration\n\n---\n\n### 4. Step Execution in cloche-agent Binary\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`: Entry point\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`: Orchestrator\n\n**Execution Flow:**\n\n1. **Runner Initialization** (`runner.go`):\n   - Reads workflow DSL from file\n   - Creates generic and prompt adapters\n   - Configures prompt adapter from env vars and workflow config\n   - Resets per-run state (attempt counts, output directory)\n\n2. **Step Executor** (`stepExecutor` in `runner.go`):\n   ```go\n   func (e *stepExecutor) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n   ```\n   - For `StepTypeScript`: Uses generic adapter, logs with `TypeScript`\n   - For `StepTypeAgent`:\n     - If has `run` config: Uses generic adapter (scripted agent)\n     - If has `prompt` config: Uses prompt adapter, copies output to `llm-<step>.log`\n   - Respects per-step `agent_command` and `agent_args` overrides\n\n3. **Engine-Driven Execution** (`/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`):\n   - Validates workflow DAG\n   - Launches steps in dependency order (can run in parallel)\n   - Follows wiring based on step results\n   - Supports fanout (one result → multiple next steps)\n   - Supports collect/join operations for synchronization\n   - Applies per-step timeout (default 30 minutes)\n\n4. **Status Reporting** (`statusReporter` in `runner.go`):\n   - Writes status to stdout (JSON for daemon consumption)\n   - Logs step start/completion to unified log\n   - Updates StatusWriter for streaming feedback\n\n---\n\n### 5. Configuration and Selection Priority\n\nAgent selection priority (highest to lowest):\n\n1. **Step-level config** (`step { agent_command = \"...\" }`)\n2. **Workflow-level config** (`container { agent_command = \"...\" }`)\n3. **Environment variable** (`CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`)\n4. **Default** (`claude`)\n\nExample workflow-level override:\n```\ncontainer {\n    agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n    agent_args = \"-p --output-format stream-json\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. DSL Syntax for Agent Steps\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`, `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`\n\n**Agent Step Syntax:**\n```\nstep implement {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  agent_command = \"claude,gemini\"      # Optional fallback chain\n  agent_args = \"-p --stream\"            # Optional arg override\n  max_attempts = \"2\"                    # Optional retry limit\n  feedback = \"true\"                     # Include validation logs in prompt\n  results = [success, fail, retry]      # Required\n}\n```\n\n**Wiring:**\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\nimplement:retry -> implement\n```\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Step type is inferred (presence of `prompt` → agent)\n- All results must be wired or handled by collect\n- Entry step is the first step declared\n- `done` and `abort` are built-in terminals\n\n---\n\n### 7. Result Protocol\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go`\n\nSteps report results via stdout marker:\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\n**Extraction Logic:**\n- Scans output for last `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` line\n- Strips all marker lines from logged output\n- If no marker found: exit code determines result (0 = success, non-0 = fail)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Container Model\n\n**File:** `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`\n\n- One container per workflow run\n- Entire project copied to `/workspace/` in container\n- `.cloche/overrides/` files applied on top\n- Results extracted via `docker cp` to git branches\n- `.git/` included so agents have context\n- Network is available (needed for API calls)\n- Auth files (`~/.claude*`) bind-mounted read-only\n\n---\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\n**Core Agent Code:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` - Interface definition\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` - Script adapter\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` - Coding agent adapter\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` - Agent runner and executor\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` - Container entrypoint\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` - Workflow DAG executor\n- `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go` - Result marker protocol\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Step and workflow types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run state tracking\n\n**Tests:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/agent/runner_test.go`\n\n**Documentation:**\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` - Workflow DSL reference\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` - Configuration and usage\n- `/workspace/AGENTS.md` - Agent instructions (project-specific)"}],"totalDurationMs":49785,"totalTokens":57730,"totalToolUseCount":36,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":655,"cache_read_input_tokens":54694,"output_tokens":2375,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":655},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
