{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JQbKuafy5CkqjsRp8SftYB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a summary of the changes made:\n\n### Changes\n\n**1. Fixed step-level agent config leaking between steps** (`internal/agent/runner.go`)\n- The `stepExecutor.Execute` method was directly mutating the shared `prompt.Adapter.Commands` and `ExplicitArgs` fields. Step-level `agent_command`/`agent_args` overrides would persist to subsequent steps, causing them to use the wrong agent.\n- Fixed by saving and restoring the original values via `defer`.\n\n**2. Added default args for well-known agents** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`)\n- Added `gemini` with `[\"-p\"]` default args\n- Added `codex` with `[\"--full-auto\"]` default args\n- Exported the map as `DefaultAgentArgs` for testability\n\n**3. Added fallback logging** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`)\n- When an agent in the fallback chain fails and the system tries the next one, it now logs: `[fallback] step \"X\": agent \"Y\" failed (...), trying \"Z\"`\n- When a fallback agent succeeds, it logs: `[fallback] step \"X\": using agent \"Y\" (primary agents failed)`\n- Uses `StatusWriter` when available, falls back to standard logger\n\n**4. New tests**\n- `TestDefaultAgentArgs_KnownAgents` - verifies default args for claude, gemini, codex\n- `TestRunner_StepLevelOverrideDoesNotLeakToNextStep` - regression test for the state leak fix (two-step workflow where step1 overrides agent_command, step2 should use workflow default)\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":275,"cache_read_input_tokens":67729,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":275},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abc5f750-0862-4f12-8214-59a5ee9bdc43","uuid":"56d7a26c-1d0b-4a09-a5f9-eea65b21772b"}
